  "prompt": "What is the stall speed and AOA of an f-14 with wings fully swept back?",
  "response": "The stall speed of the F-14 Tomcat with its wings fully swept back (which is at the 0\u00b0 position) can vary based on a number of factors, including weight, configuration, and altitude. However, for a typical F-14 configuration at a reasonable weight, the stall speed in clean configuration (flaps and gear up) is approximately 136-140 knots.\n\nThe angle of attack (AOA) at which the F-14 stalls with wings fully swept back is usually around 15-18 degrees, but this can vary based on specific flight conditions and aircraft configuration.\n\nRemember, these values can vary based on many factors, so they should be considered approximate. For precise data, consult official flight manuals or technical specifications from the manufacturer.",
